reviewText: D​on't take this course! Mailchimp has a NEW online platform. This online tutorial uses the OLD platform.
website provided is not working
T​he course needs to be updated to the newest version of Mailchimp.
Too short and needs more details, its outdated now too.

I was expecting so much more.  For example how to create segments and send separate emails to the different segments.  The platform view provided to practice my email campaign on was SO different from the tutor's view that I had to sign into Mailchimp on a different tab on my own computer in order to actually complete the steps.  I therefore had to switch between the two screens.   The tutor also seemed to be looking for the buttons/links/tabs to click on - it was not done smoothly.  Very frustrating course.
Not So informative, anybody could do it even without a course, atleast when you are doing a single guided project do a difficult one which include all the command.
It's an easy-to-follow course but it needs to be updated. Mail chimp seems to have changed their website layout and tabs.
You should make it clearer where to get emails for the test campaign from, or provide some test addresses.

I had an account with mailchimp last time but wasn't able to learn and apply it until I enrolled this course. This is so timely, Thank you, Coursera!

the guided project was good. It just happens that the instructor dashboard shows different version of the site compare to mine, making it hard for someone like me who is a beginner in using mailchimp to follow the instruction. But, the intention and the idea of the guided project is very good.

The instructor did a good job explaining everything, however the website/software has been updated since the video was made, so some of the pages/functions/etc. were not where they were shown in the video. Fortunately, it wasn't too hard to figure out where to find things that weren't in the same place, however the instructional videos should be updated to avoid confusing students.

Helpful for someone with NO experience using Mailchimp at all, but other than that, the course didn't teach me how to use Mailchimp as in depth as I expected. Instructor was to the point, but again just too short of a course for my liking.
